news.title: New realty launches in top seven cities to rise 6-9% in FY26: ICRA
news.para: The launches are estimated to have sharply declined by 14-17% in 2024-25 due to approval-related challenges, after reporting the highest ever at 701 million sq ft in the previous year.

news.title: Private equity inflow in Indian real estate down 3% to $3.7 billion in FY25: Anarock
news.para: As per the data, the PE investments in real estate declined to USD 3.7 billion in 2024-25 from USD 3.8 billion in the preceding year.

news.title: Revolutionizing Real Estate CRM with BuilderOpedia
news.para: Manras Technologies has won the ‘PropTech CRM Solution’ award by The Economic Times Real Estate Awards.

news.title: Macrotech Developers reports pre-sales of ₹48.1 billion in Q4 FY25
news.para: With this, Macrotech Developers has achieved pre-sales of ₹176.3 billion in FY25 (up 21% year-on-year), surpassing our FY25 guidance and recording 20% growth.

news.title: Hours into new fiscal year, Lucknow civic body sees Rs 2 crore house tax collection
news.para: According to LMC officials, the website was opened for a limited time on Saturday afternoon, during which more than 8,000 citizens paid their house tax online.

news.title: Mumbai gears up for stricter construction waste rules from April 2026
news.para: ​With the new regulations, construction practices in Mumbai must transition from untracked dumping to a monitored and accountable system. The responsibility now lies with the BMC to implement and enforce these measures.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body to undertake survey of unauthorised buildings
news.para: This process involves issuing notices to concerned property holders, conducting hearings for their perspectives, and issuing final orders.

news.title: Nashik civic body serves notices to 70 developers for not maintaining traffic islands
news.para: Under its Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) initiative, the NMC has developed a total of 100 traffic islands on a build, develop, repair, and maintain basis.

news.title: Pune-based builder falls for returns bait on investment, loses Rs 6.3 crore
news.para: The victim lodged a complaint with Deccan Gymkhana police and the case was taken over by the Pune police's Economic Offences Wing (EOW) for further investigation on Friday night.

news.title: Telangana RERA orders refund for buyers over delayed project at Gopanpally
news.para: ​The refund is to be made along with an interest of 11% per annum from the date of the Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) until the date of realization. Orders were issued on March 28 and 29.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRDA approves additional plot in BKC to NSE for Rs 758 crore
news.para: The plot, C-82 in G-block, has permissible built-up space of 22,000sqm and will be leased for 80 years for commercial use.

news.title: Uploading of occupancy & completion certificates on Odisha RERA website must
news.para: The completion certificate is a legal document testifying that a building is constructed adhering to all set norms. The occupancy certificate establishes that a building is fit to move in and live for the occupants.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC asks MDDA vice-chairman to clarify stand on illegal constructions
news.para: ​The Garhwal commissioner and the Mussoorie-Dehradun Development Authority (MDDA) vice-chairman appeared before a division bench of Chief Justice G Narendar and Justice Pankaj Purohit via videoconferencing.

news.title: Belagavi civic body approves 3% increase in property tax
news.para: The meeting deliberated on key civic issues, particularly the city's drinking water crisis and obstacles in e-khata registrations, and approved a three percent increase in property tax.

news.title: Nagpur, Kamptee get land survey centres
news.para: These state-of-the-art centres, set up by the Land Records Department, will offer citizens a hassle-free and time-bound solution for all land-related services under one roof, at affordable govt-fixed rates.

news.title: Bengaluru: Shivaram Karanth Layout project lags with 40% infra work pending
news.para: ​While most blocks have been marked, crossroads have been built, and streetlights installed in certain areas, key infrastructure like main roads, water supply, and underground drainage systems remain incomplete.

news.title: High court upholds land acquisition by Bengaluru development body for layout expansion
news.para: From 750 acres acquired under the final notification, BDA formed 5,991 residential sites of different dimensions, with 4,983 already allotted to various applicants.

news.title: Manesar civic body chief directs officials to serve notices & seal tax defaulters’ properties
news.para: Officials were instructed to install new streetlights and repair non-functional ones in the corporation area and ensure fogging in all villages.
